  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Tower Crane Operator (Luffing Jib / Saddle Jib)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>• Operate tower crane (luffing jib/saddle jib) safely and efficiently to hoist and move materials around at construction sites</p>\n<p>• Conduct daily pre-operation checks and ensure equipment is in good working condition</p>\n<p>• Follow approved lifting plans and site safety procedures at all times</p>\n<p>• Coordinate closely with lifting supervisors and signalmen to perform lifts accurately</p>\n<p>• Monitor crane performance and report any faults or safety issues immediately</p>\n<p>• Maintain proper records of crane operations and safety inspections</p>\n<p>• May be required to work overtime (OT), Sundays, and Public Holidays as part of the job scope</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>• Valid Tower Crane Operator License recognized by the Ministry of Manpower (MOM) / Building and Construction Authority (BCA)</p>\n<p>• At least 2-3 years of experience operating luffing jib/saddle jib tower cranes</p>\n<p>• Good understanding of lifting plans, load charts, and safety procedures</p>\n<p>• Physically fit and alert during operation</p>\n<p>• Able to work at height and in outdoor construction environments</p>\n<p>• Familiar with WSH regulations and safety standards in Singapore</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Salary</strong></p>\n<p>•\tEstimated $7,000 – $8,000 per month, inclusive of estimated overtime (OT)</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Annual Leave</strong></p>\n<p>•\t10 days annual leave for the first year</p>\n<p>•\tIncrease by 1 day per year from the second year, up to a maximum of 14 days</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Medical Benefits</strong></p>\n<p>•\t14 days outpatient MC (Medical Certificate) per year</p>\n<p>•\tMedical claims up to $300/year with valid receipts</p>",
